symptoms of rohypnol:

- quick intoxication
- bloodshot eyes
- disorientation
- memory loss

it’s a common misconception that roofie drugs make you paralyzed the whole time. it’s very possible to still be moving.

the effects are amplified by alcohol but it can be put in ANY drink. this includes water, juice, and soda. it causes sedation, loss of inhibitions, blacking out, amnesia, and severe disorientation. takes effect after 15-30mins of ingestion and can last as long as 6-12 hours

although, the creator changed it so if rohypnol is mixed into a clear drink it can make it appear blue so it’s easier to spot. 

it’s difficult to predict the effects of any drug on an individual, sense it depends on the dosage, alcohol consumption, and your body's metabolism.

it’s easily dissolvable in almost any kind of drink making it easily undetectable. it’s colorless, odorless, and tasteless so if you didn’t see someone put it in your drink, then you would never know you were spiked until the next day.
